  "properties": {
    "encrypted": "false",
    "instructions_important": "false",
    "long_instructions": "#### Surprising Effects \r\n\r\n**Define:** Choose a song with a strong, repeating beat. Your challenge is to surprise your listeners by placing a short sound effect just before each beat ends. These effects can be dramatic, subtle, or even funny - it's up to you!\r\n\r\n![](https://images.code.org/006d907c692bb18b5e6e9be299b14b10-image-1744151092143.png)\r\n\r\n**Prepare:** Pick a song with a clear beat. Plan at least 3 different beat + effect combinations. Think carefully about when each effect should play so it lands just before the end of the beat.\r\n\r\nIf you want to pick a new song, you can click the restart button in the upper-right corner [<i class=\"fa-solid fa-lightbulb\"></i> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-square-right\"></i>](#clickable=start-over-button)\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#ebe8f1; border: 0; border-radius: 10px; clear:both; padding: 5px\">\r\n\r\n**Musical Suggestions:**\r\n- *\"Chantaje\" - Shakira ft. Maluma* (great Latin rhythms and strong endings)\r\n- *\"I Like to Move It\" - will.i.am* (clear beats, fun to interrupt)\r\n- *\"Wake Me Up\" - Aloe Blacc* (mixes acoustic and percussive beats)\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n**Try:** Create 3 unique beat + effect combinations. Use sequencing to place the effect just before the beat ends, adding a rhythmic twist that feels intentional.\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#ebe8f1; border: 0; border-radius: 10px; clear:both; padding: 5px\">\r\n\r\nNeed some help? Try the [<i class=\"fa-solid fa-book\"></i> Docs](#clickable=documentation-button) in the upper-right corner!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n**Reflect:** Do your effects create surprise while still feeling musical? How did the timing affect the groove? In order to complete this level, your remix must include:\r\n\r\n- 3 unique beat tracks\r\n- 3 unique effect tracks\r\n- Each effect played just before a beat ends\r\n",
    "offer_browser_tts": "true",
    "use_secondary_finish_button": "false",
    "hide_share_and_remix": "true",
